Package nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.python

package nusri.fyp.demo.service.img_sender.python
This package contains the services related to the EOID (presumably an external image data service or system). The classes in this package manage image data specifically targeted at the EOID service for processing. These services handle communication with EOID, sending image data, and possibly receiving processed results, and also support specific configurations or optimizations for EOID interactions.

    ImageSenderOfPython
    Implementation of ImageSenderService for sending image frames to a backend Python server (EOID) for inference.
    PythonServerLoadBalancer
    Service responsible for load balancing among multiple Python server instances.
    This class maintains a list of Python server instances (each with its own queue size and port) and periodically fetches updated information about them.
    PythonServerLoadBalancer.Instance
    Represents a single Python server instance.
    Each instance has: A queue size (string representation) indicating how many tasks are queued. A port number where the instance is listening for requests.
    PythonServerLoadBalancer.InstancesResponse
    Represents the response structure returned by the /instances endpoint.
    Contains a list of PythonServerLoadBalancer.Instance objects detailing queue sizes and ports for each Python instance.
